<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="307" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1436,2001]" pageId="10" pageNumber="307">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,600,1436,1461]" pageId="10" pageNumber="307">Diagnosis of the hitherto unknown Ƌ:</emphasis>
The male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tkalcu" authorityYear="1999" box="[748,858,1437,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplosmia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picena">
<emphasis box="[748,768,1437,1460]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="307">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[783,858,1437,1460]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="307">picena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by an emarginate spine on sternum 1. The only other 
<emphasis box="[349,377,1472,1495]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="307">O.</emphasis>
(
<taxonomicName box="[393,516,1471,1496]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplosmia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[393,516,1471,1496]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="307">Hoplosmia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) species with this character are 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Müller" authorityYear="2018" box="[873,1031,1472,1496]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Osmia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="10" pageNumber="307" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="centaureae">
<emphasis box="[873,893,1472,1495]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="307">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[907,1031,1473,1496]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="307">centaureae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1811" box="[1084,1224,1472,1496]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Osmia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="10" pageNumber="307" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spinigera">
<emphasis box="[1084,1104,1472,1495]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="307">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1118,1224,1473,1496]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="307">spinigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which differ from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tkalcu" authorityYear="1999" box="[151,263,1509,1532]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplosmia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picena">
<emphasis box="[151,171,1509,1532]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="307">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[188,263,1509,1532]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="307">picena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the distinctly coarser and denser punctation of terga and sterna and by the longer ocellooccipital distance (see Key to species).
</paragraph>
